## Conversation
User asked to add backwards compatibility for GitHub PR #7488, then asked to rebase and push. PR #7488 renamed Conversation SDK span factory methods on Turn/SubAgent from llm/tool/subagent to start_llm/start_tool/start_subagent. The compatibility goal was to preserve existing callers of the old method names while keeping the new names canonical.

## Actions
Inspected current branch hatchery/overseer and PR #7488 commit fc23275e76. Applied the PR diff locally. Added deprecated wrappers in weave/conversation/conversation.py: Turn.llm, Turn.tool, Turn.subagent, SubAgent.llm, and SubAgent.tool. Added tests in tests/conversation/test_deprecation.py to assert each old method emits DeprecationWarning and forwards arguments to the corresponding start_* method. Ran focused conversation tests and ruff lint/format. After permissions changed to full access, staged the real worktree with normal git and created this commit.

